<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-09-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-09-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="570" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d570">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Raikes</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Adee</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">British
                                        Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Bar Harbor,
                                    Me.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-09-05"><hi rend="italic">September 5,
                                    1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Lord Lansdowne desires me to express on behalf of His Majesty’s
                            Government their heartfelt congratulations on the President’s merciful
                            escape from serious injury.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Raikes</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>